quran[50]{c,v,t}:
  15,50,and that my woe is the grievous woe
  15,51,And inform them concerning Abraham's guests
  15,52,"when they entered in unto him and said, 'Peace!' he said, 'Verily, we are afraid of you"
  15,53,"They said, 'Be not afraid! verily, we give thee glad tidings of a knowing boy"
  15,54,"He said, 'Do ye give me this glad tidings although old age has touched me? give me the glad tidings then"
  15,55,"They said, 'We give the glad tidings of the truth, then be not of those who despair"
  15,56,"He said, 'Who would despair of the mercy of his Lord save those who err"
  15,57,"He said, 'What is your business, O ye messengers"
  15,58,"They said, 'Verily, we are sent unto a sinful people"
  15,59,"save only Lot's family, them will we save all together"
  15,60,"except his wife; we have decreed, verily, she shall be of those who linger"
  15,61,And when the messengers came unto Lot's family
  15,62,"he said, 'Verily, ye are a people whom I recognise not"
  15,63,"They said, 'Nay, but we have come to thee with that whereof they did doubt"
  15,64,"And we have brought thee the truth, and, verily, we speak the truth"
  15,65,"Travel then with thy family in the deep darkness of the night, and follow thou their rear; and let not any one of you turn round to look; but go on to where ye are bidden"
  15,66,And we decided for him this affair because the uttermost one of these people should be cut off on the morrow
  15,67,"Then the people of the city came, clad at the tidings"
  15,68,"Said he, 'Verily, these are my guests, therefore disgrace me not"
  15,69,"but fear God, and put me not to shame"
  15,70,"They said, 'Have we not forbidden thee everybody in the world"
  15,71,"He said, 'Here are my daughters, if do it ye must"
  15,72,"By thy life! verily, they were surely in their intoxication blindly wandering on"
  15,73,And the noise caught them at the dawn
  15,74,"And we made the higher parts (of the cities) their lower parts, and rained down on them stones of baked clay"
  15,75,"Verily, in that is a sign to those who mark"
  15,76,"And, verily, the (cities) are on a path that still remains"
  15,77,"Verily, in that is a sign to the believers"
  15,78,And the fellows of the Grove too were unjust
  15,79,"and we took vengeance on them, and, verily, they both are for an obvious example"
  15,80,And the fellows of El 'Hagr called the messengers liars
  15,81,"and we brought them our signs, but they therefrom did turn away"
  15,82,And they did hew them in the mountain houses to dwell in in safety
  15,83,But the noise caught them in the morn
  15,84,and that which they had earned availed them naught
  15,85,"We did not create the heavens and the earth and all that is between them both, save in truth. And, verily, the Hour is surely coming; then do thou pardon with a fair pardon"
  15,86,"Verily, thy Lord He is the creator, the knowing"
  15,87,"We have already brought thee Seven of the Repetition, and the mighty Qur'an"
  15,88,"Let not thine eyes strain after what we have allowed a few pairs of them to enjoy, nor grieve for them; but lower thy wing to the believers"
  15,89,"and say, 'Verily, I am an obvious warner"
  15,90,As we sent down (punishment) on the separatists
  15,91,who dismember the Qur'an
  15,92,"But, by thy Lord! we will question them, one and all"
  15,93,about what they have done
  15,94,"Therefore, publish what thou art bidden, and turn aside from the idolaters"
  15,95,"Verily, we are enough for thee against the scoffers"
  15,96,Who place with God other gods; but they at length shall know
  15,97,And we knew that thy breast was straitened at what they say
  15,98,"Then celebrate the praises of thy Lord, and be thou of those who adore"
  15,99,And serve thy Lord until the certainty shall come to thee